<span id="freeTextContainer6243250310989898500">I really don&apos;t get why people consider Kathleen E Woodiwiss to be the queen of historical romance? I mean I have only read two of her novels and I can honestly say that she was nowhere near as good as other talented authors such as Judith Mcnaught and Laurie Mcbain. This book for instance is utter shite, full of stupid one dimensional characters with a pointless storyline that just drags on and on. <br/><br/>Don&apos;t waste your precious time reading this crap, you will only be sorry!</span>
  <span id="freeText6243250310989898500" style="display:none">I really don't get why people consider Kathleen E Woodiwiss to be the queen of historical romance? I mean I have only read two of her novels and I can honestly say that she was nowhere near as good as other talented authors such as Judith Mcnaught and Laurie Mcbain. This book for instance is utter shite, full of stupid one dimensional characters with a pointless storyline that just drags on and on. <br /><br />Don't waste your precious time reading this crap, you will only be sorry!</span>
