        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1320950227" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18398553008035143890">I read this years ago when I was probably a young teenager. I loved this book then. As I read it now I am (a bit) aghast at the fact that Brandon basically raped Heather and took her virginity and he did it again. I don&apos;t think that will fly in modern times like these.<br/><br/>Of course I read somewhere that this is one of (if not the first) original &apos;bodice rippers&apos;. I guess it would be since it was first published in 1972. <br/><br/>**Last read on 7/1/2015**<br/>I still love this book. Not sure why I had it at 4 star</span>
  <span id="freeText18398553008035143890" style="display:none">I read this years ago when I was probably a young teenager. I loved this book then. As I read it now I am (a bit) aghast at the fact that Brandon basically raped Heather and took her virginity and he did it again. I don't think that will fly in modern times like these.<br /><br />Of course I read somewhere that this is one of (if not the first) original 'bodice rippers'. I guess it would be since it was first published in 1972. <br /><br />**Last read on 7/1/2015**<br />I still love this book. Not sure why I had it at 4 stars when it is one of the classic Kathleen Woodiwiss book. I'm changing my rating to 5 stars. I think it is because now I read a lot of erotica and the sex scenes here are very tame, but I think the book as a whole has a great story so if I judged the story by itself it would have 5 stars so I'm changing it to 5 stars.</span>
